The '''I'''ndependent '''L'''ubricant '''M'''anufacturer '''A'''ssociation ('''ILMA''') was established in 1948 it is a members only trade organization that represents the interests of [[lubricant]] manufacturers. The word "independent" in the name indicates that Integrated Oil Companies ([[Big Oil]]) are not members however most of them are ILMA sponsors.

