{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2013}} {{Infobox person |name = Marin Karmitz |image = Bayrou Bercy 2007-04-18 n14.jpg |image_size = |caption = Karmitz in 2007. |birth_name = |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1938|10|7}} |birth_place = [[Bucharest]], Romania |death_date = |death_place = |death_cause = |resting_place = |resting_place_coordinates = |residence = |nationality = French |other_names = |known_for = |education = |alma_mater = [[Institut des hautes études cinématographiques]] |employer = |occupation = Film producer, film distributor, [[film exhibitor]], director |home_town = |title = |salary = |networth = |height = |weight = |term = |predecessor = |successor = |party = |boards = |religion = |spouse = |partner = |children = |parents = |relations = |signature = |website = |footnotes = }}
'''Marin Karmitz''' (born 7 October 1938) is a French businessman whose career has spanned the [[Cinema of France|French film industry]], including director, producer, film distributor, and operator of a [[Movie theater|chain of cinemas]].<ref>{{cite web|work=[[The New York Times]]|title=Marin Karmitz|url=https://movies.nytimes.com/person/96792/Marin-Karmitz}}</ref>
Karmitz attended film school at [[IDHEC]]<ref name="Brody2009">{{cite book|last=Brody|first=Richard|title=Everything Is Cinema: The Working Life of Jean-Luc Godard|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HD1KAipFwQ4C&pg=PA129|accessdate=8 June 2012|date=23 June 2009|publisher=Macmillan|isbn=9780805080155|pages=129–}}</ref> (renamed [[La Fémis]]) and worked as a director of photography after graduating.
Karmitz founded MK2, a [[production company]] and movie theater chain, which has specialized in creating, distributing, and screening independent or [[auteur theory|"auteurist"]] cinema, including short films.
In 2005, he turned over leadership of the MK2 company and its theaters to his son, Nathanaël.{{citation needed|date=August 2013}}
==Exhibitions== • 2010:"Un parcours dans la collection de Marin Karmitz", exhibited at [[:fr:Rencontres d'Arles|Rencontres d'Arles]] festival, France.
